{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.7",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 7 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:1",
      "text": "My son, keep my words. Lay up my commandments within you.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:2",
      "text": "Keep my commandments and live! Guard my teaching as the apple of your eye.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:3",
      "text": "Bind them on your fingers. Write them on the tablet of your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:4",
      "text": "Tell wisdom, “You are my sister.” Call understanding your relative,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:5",
      "text": "that they may keep you from the strange woman, from the foreigner who flatters with her words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:6",
      "text": "For at the window of my house, I looked out through my lattice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:7",
      "text": "I saw among the simple ones. I discerned among the youths a young man void of understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:8",
      "text": "passing through the street near her corner, he went the way to her house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:9",
      "text": "in the twilight, in the evening of the day, in the middle of the night and in the darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:10",
      "text": "Behold, there a woman met him with the attire of a prostitute, and with crafty intent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:11",
      "text": "She is loud and defiant. Her feet don’t stay in her house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:12",
      "text": "Now she is in the streets, now in the squares, and lurking at every corner.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:13",
      "text": "So she caught him, and kissed him. With an impudent face she said to him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:14",
      "text": "“Sacrifices of peace offerings are with me. Today I have paid my vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:15",
      "text": "Therefore I came out to meet you, to diligently seek your face, and I have found you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:16",
      "text": "I have spread my couch with carpets of tapestry, with striped cloths of the yarn of Egypt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:17",
      "text": "I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:18",
      "text": "Come, let’s take our fill of loving until the morning. Let’s solace ourselves with loving.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:19",
      "text": "For my husband isn’t at home. He has gone on a long journey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:20",
      "text": "He has taken a bag of money with him. He will come home at the full moon.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:21",
      "text": "With persuasive words, she led him astray. With the flattering of her lips, she seduced him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:22",
      "text": "He followed her immediately, as an ox goes to the slaughter, as a fool stepping into a noose.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:23",
      "text": "Until an arrow strikes through his liver, as a bird hurries to the snare, and doesn’t know that it will cost his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:24",
      "text": "Now therefore, sons, listen to me. Pay attention to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:25",
      "text": "Don’t let your heart turn to her ways. Don’t go astray in her paths,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:26",
      "text": "for she has thrown down many wounded. Yes, all her slain are a mighty army.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.7.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:27",
      "text": "Her house is the way to Sheol, going down to the rooms of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
